{"questionId":"17544","questionHtml":"<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>The Malthouse Charity Run is a <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>5</mn></math> kilometre race. The time taken for each runner to complete&nbsp;the race was recorded. The data was found to be normally distributed with a mean time of&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>28</mn></math> minutes and a standard deviation of <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>5</mn></math> minutes.</p>\n<p>A runner who completed the race is chosen at random.</p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-leaf-prompt\"><p>Write down the probability that the runner completed the race in more than <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>28</mn></math> minutes.</p></div>","markschemeHtml":"<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>5</mn><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mfenced><mrow><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mn>2</mn></mfrac><mo>,</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mn>50</mn><mo>%</mo></mrow></mfenced></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;<em><strong>(A1) (C1)</strong></em></p>\n<p><em><strong><span class=\"mjpage\">[1 mark]</span></strong></em></p>","meta":{"questionId":"17544","referenceCode":"19N.1.SL.TZ0.T_12a","subjectId":"51-dp-mathematics-applications-and-interpretation","title":"Write down the probability that the runner completed the race in more than 28 minutes.","paper":"1","level":"SL","questionNumber":"a","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 1]","breadcrumbLabels":["Topic 4—Statistics and probability","Topic 4—Statistics and probability","SL 4.9—Normal distribution and calculations"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}},"schemaVersion":2}